# toolchain fragment — one line per tool:  <mise-name>  <command>  [description]
#   col 1   installed via `mise use -g`
#   col 2   command the session-context fragment probes with `command -v`
#   col 3+  description; if present, the tool is advertised in the session context
# The installer + inventory read the UNION of every /opt/toolchain/tools.d/*.list,
# so add tools by shipping ANOTHER fragment (no need to copy this one). Blank lines
# and #-comments are ignored.
#
# Deliberately lean + generic — a profile adds its own kit via a fragment
# (see overlay/50-example/tools.d/extras.list for an example).
uv          uv        Python envs/deps/run (prefer over pip & venv)
github-cli  gh        GitHub CLI — PRs, issues, API
ripgrep     rg        ripgrep — fast content search
fd          fd        fast file find (prefer over find)
